name: #22. Sandy “Scribbles” Katana
description:
Every club needs great scribes and poets. Part-time blogger and haiku beat poet, Sandy “Scribbles” Katana is just not one of them. But what she lacks in rhyme, she more than makes up for in cuteness and charm. 

AGMs gone wild
Pen mightier than the sword
I take club minutes

I look to the sky
And contemplate existence
I am a bunny.

--------------------------------------------------

"What can travel all around the world without leaving its corner?"
"I have cities, but no houses. I have mountains, but no trees. I have water, but no fish. What am I?"
"The more of this there is, the less you see. What is it?"
"What has many teeth, but cannot bite?"

'r' toggles auto-rotate.
